parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding doors can cause the doors to open or close unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, and making it difficult for passengers to exit the vehicle in an emergency.
symptoms: The power sliding doors do not open or close properly
the doors open or close unexpectedly
the doors are difficult to open or close manually
the cables are frayed or broken
the doors do not latch properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting and cracking of the dashboard can cause a distraction while driving, leading to accidents, and can also cause breathing issues due to the smell of melted rubber.
symptoms: The dashboard is melting or cracking
the dashboard is sticky
the dashboard is malleable
there is a strong smell of melted rubber.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the lift-gate frame can cause the lift-gate to become unsecured while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The lift-gate frame is cracking
the lift-gate is unsecured while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding door can cause the door to become stuck or inoperable, posing a safety risk to occupants, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door may not open or close
may open or close unexpectedly
or may require manual force to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal may feel soft or spongy
the brakes may engage unexpectedly
or the vehicle may experience grinding noises when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety features to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The warning lights may illuminate
the air conditioner may not function properly
or the vehicle may experience electrical shorts or fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch handle can cause the hatch to become stuck or inoperable, posing a safety risk to occupants, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The rear hatch handle may become soft or pliable
making it difficult to open or close the hatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift cable can cause the vehicle to roll away, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shift lever can be moved without the ignition key
the vehicle can roll away even when in park
and the parking brake may need to be applied to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without pressing the gas pedal
the engine RPM increases rapidly
and the vehicle may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or slips
the engine RPM increases rapidly
and the vehicle may not respond to acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VVT-i gear can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the VSC and TRAC OFF lights come on
and the engine may stall or seize.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle may not respond to shifting.
